<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="64" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,965,1477]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,312,1330,1356]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64">Remarks</emphasis>
Before Vera­Pelez J.L., et al (2000) clearly distinguished the two species, they were often confused. In some previously published papers, the two species were confused as same species (
<bibRefCitation author="Powell" box="[1267,1429,1371,1397]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" pagination="1 - 184" refId="ref3292" refString="Powell A. W. B. (1966) The molluscan families Speightiidae and Turridae. Bulletin of the Auckland Institute and Museum, 5, 1 - 184, 23 plates." type="book chapter" year="1966">Powell, 1966</bibRefCitation>
; Springsteen F. J. &amp; F. M. Leobrera, 1986; 
<bibRefCitation author="Okutani" box="[672,847,1411,1437]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" pagination="619 - 667" refId="ref3198" refString="Okutani T. (2000) Marine Mollusks in Japan. Tokai University Press, Tokyo, p. 619 - 667." type="book chapter" year="2000">Okutani, 2000</bibRefCitation>
). In 
<collectingCountry box="[916,989,1411,1437]" name="China" pageId="1" pageNumber="64">China</collectingCountry>
, Tsi Chung­yen et al (1983 &amp; 2004) reported this species as 
<taxonomicName authority="(Larmarck)" baseAuthorityName="Larmarck" baseAuthorityYear="1816" box="[429,726,1451,1477]" class="Gastropoda" family="Turridae" genus="Turris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="crispa">
<emphasis box="[429,581,1451,1476]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="64">Turris crispa</emphasis>
(Larmarck)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
